# LLM Wiki ↔ TakeOne (TakeOneBrain)

Wiki project: `~/Desktop/Brain/TakeOneBrain` (separate from this git repo).  
Project ID: `d878c348-4e81-4259-90e5-6fd21404f59f`

## Start of every turn — read wiki

Before planning or editing:

```bash
bash .cursor/scripts/fetch-llm-wiki-context.sh "<short paraphrase of user request>"
```

If output says **skipped**, mention once, then continue. Cite wiki paths when using hits (`wiki/...`, `raw/sources/...`).

## End of every turn — write wiki (mandatory)

After **every** user prompt in this project — including Q&A, reviews, and small edits — append a session note so TakeOneBrain stays current:

```bash
bash .cursor/scripts/append-llm-wiki-session.sh --topic <website|components|events|deployment|architecture|general> <<'EOF'
## User request
(one line)

## What we did / answered
(bullets — include conclusions even if no files changed)

## Files / areas
(key paths, or "none")

## Decisions / follow-ups
(if any)
EOF
```

Pick `--topic` from the main area touched. The script saves under `raw/sources/cursor-sessions/` and triggers LLM Wiki **rescan** when `LLM_WIKI_API_TOKEN` is set and the app is running.

Tell the user the wiki path printed (`LLM_WIKI_APPEND_OK: ...`) in one short line.

`afterFileEdit` hook adds **Files touched** automatically from `.cursor/wiki-edits-buffer.log`.

## Do not

- Log or echo `LLM_WIKI_API_TOKEN`.
- Put secrets in wiki notes.
- Skip the append step at end of turn.

## Setup

```bash
export LLM_WIKI_API_TOKEN="…"   # LLM Wiki → Settings → API Server
```

Add to `~/.zshrc`. Keep LLM Wiki desktop app open. Open **TakeOneBrain** in LLM Wiki (or rely on hardcoded project ID in scripts).
